The paper proposes a novel hybrid architecture for coordinating networked robots in sensing and information routing applications. The paper focuses on the optimization of wireless network through mobility of robots. Therefore, the most likely category is Robotics (cs.RO). The paper also deals with information flow and routing, which falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper proposes a control plane for regulating information flow, which falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also uses potential-based control to guide the robots, which falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.MA). Finally, the paper proposes a formulation that generates feedback between routing and sensing needs, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
